@Bardi07it is absolutely obvious that they are lunching almost similar products every year so they can charge clients a lot of money for the same product they lunched years ago. 
The problem with iOS is that at some point they will stop making software updates for the previews models, therefor you are obliged to upgrade to a new phone only for this reason, if not for other reasons, because apps like youtube are no longer available for the older phones.
In terms of capabilities, it is clear that this year they upgraded the camera functions a lot and for this reason only it would be a good investment for some who can afford this insane price.
